  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>
      rts2-xfocusc display image acquired from CCDs which are part of RTS2 system. It can be used to
      interactively focusc camera.
    </para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <para>
      These programs follow the usual &gnu; command line syntax,
      with long options starting with two dashes (`-').  A summary of
      options is included below.
    </para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-h</option></term>
        <term><option>--help</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show summary of options.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--version</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show version of program.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--server <replaceable class="parameter">central server hostname</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Change central server location. Defaults to localhost.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--port <replaceable class="parameter">port number</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Change central server port number. Default value is specified with compilation, default is 617.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--config <replaceable class="parameter">server name</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Specify configuration file. Defaults to <filename>/etc/rts2/rts2.ini</filename>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
